<p align="left">Regrettably, it is not clear from his letter what the award itself was. Nor is it clear what the organizations were which had sponsored the nomination. Yet it seems likely that this was for the AERA-PDK Award for Distinguished Contributions to Research in Education, jointly bestowed by the American Educational Research Association and Phi-Delta-Kappa between 1964 and 1974, which Piaget and Inhelder received in Chicago in February of 1968. Confirmation of these details will almost certainly be found among the materials currently in storage.</p></fn>
